title: Replies to initial written questions raised by Finance Committee Members in examining the Estimates of Expenditure 2007-08
question_text: According to the indicators of this programme, the estimated expenditure on refurbishment and improvement for 2007 is $2,341.9 million, a decrease of $249.7 million or 9%, compared with the actual expenditure of $2,591.6 million in 2006. Would the Government account for the significant decrease in such expenditure?
reply_text: : The estimated provision for refurbishment and improvement works in 2006-07 and 2007-08 is $2,420 million and $2,450 million respectively. Hence, the provisions are in fact similar in terms of financial year. The decrease in the estimated expenditure for calendar year 2007 over the actual expenditure for calendar year 2006 is mainly due to the difference in the expenditure pattern of the projects concerned. Many of the projects in 2005-06 were carried out during the period from January to March 2006 to meetthe operational needs of client departments, the expenditure of which was therefore reflected in calendar year 2006. Another reason for the higher actual expenditure in calendar year 2006 was due to the early implementation of the planned energy enhancement projects scheduled for 2006-07 to support the government’s initiative in energy saving. These two factors which have contributed to the higher expenditure in calendar year 2006 are unique to that calendar year and are not expected to be applicable in calendar year 2007. We therefore expect the expenditure in calendar year 2007 to be lower than that in calendar year 2006. Signature Name in block letters C. H. YUE Post Title Director of Architectural Services Date 14 March 2007
